This is the vimfiles that I use.  It uses Tim Pope's awesome Pathogen library
to manage vim bundles in a sane and separated manner for easy addition and
removal of bundles.  This has only been tested on Mac OS X.

Current bundles used are:
  vim-ruby:
    vim-ruby
  vim-scripts:
    AutoTag,jQuery,matchit.zip,Gist.vim,IndexedSearch,Color-Sampler-Pack,
    ColorSchemeMenuMaker,ScrollColors,xterm16.vim,netrw.vim,ZoomWin
  tpope:
    vim-cucumber,vim-fugitive,vim-git,vim-haml,vim-markdown,vim-repeat,
    vim-unimpaired,vim-surround,vim-vividchalk
  RubidiumStudios:
    vim-rails (fork of tpope's vim-rails with the menu restored)
  jpalardy:
    vim-slime
  lucapette:
    vim-jquery-doc,vim-ruby-doc
  astashov:
    vim-ruby-debugger
  kchmck:
    vim-coffee-script
  msanders:
    snipmate.vim
  godlygeek:
    tabular
  scrooloose:
    nerdtreei,nerdcommenter,snipmate-snippets
  jistr:
    vim-nerdtree-tabs
  timcharper:
    textile.vim
  mileszs:
    ack.vim
  reinh:
    vim-makegreen
  wincent:
    Command-TA

INSTALLATION
============

Run the following commands in your $HOME directory (backup your existing
.vimrd, .gvimrc, and .vim/ files first) 

git clone git://github.com/RubidiumStudios/dot-vim.git .vim
ln -sin .vim/.vimrc .vimrc
ln -sin .vim/.gvimrc .gvimrc
cd .vim
ruby update_bundles

TODO
====

The scrooloose snippets are currently disabled because they conflict with the
existing snipmate default snippets -- if you want to use them and don't mind
the warnings generated every time you open a file, uncomment the
scrooloose/snipmate-snippets section at the bottom of update_bundles

